The paper deals with the problem of community detection and prediction in evolving networks with content, which is a common problem in social media analysis and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also proposes a shared factorization model that uses both content and structure, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques such as latent semantic analysis, which is a common technique in the field of information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also deals with the temporal analysis of the network, which falls under the category of software development (cs.SD). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques such as text embedding, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
